1. Both the questionid and optionid should be correct. If the questionid id not present in DB, error will be sent in the response
2. Valid links will be established. The response will include the questions that have valid links and the errors for which link could not be established due to inaccurate data sent in request

RESPONSE CODES : 
200 - OK
400 - BAD REQUEST


======================================================================================================================



HTTP METHOD : GET

URI : /getquestion?questionid="123344"

QUERY PARAMS 

questionid : 5f08ac5fc6d09839608940f3

(We will send nextquestionid to this route)

RESPONSE JSON STRUCTURE

{
    "question": {
        "_id": "5f08ac5fc6d09839608940f3",
        "isFirstQuestion": false,
        "questiontext": "Time to start the trip",
        "optionstype": "MCQ",
        "options": [
            {
                "nextquestionid": "5f08ac5fc6d09839608940f6",
                "_id": "5f08ac5fc6d09839608940f4",
                "text": "Start trip",
                "isValidOption": true,
                "score": 10
            },
            {
                "nextquestionid": null,
                "_id": "5f08ac5fc6d09839608940f5",
                "text": "Dont start",
                "isValidOption": false,
                "score": 0
            }
        ],
        "__v": 0
    }
}


RESPONSE CODES:

200 - OK
400 - Bad request
500 - Server error






